This paper deals with the capacity of a binary erasure channel with feedback, which is a classic problem in information theory and falls under the umbrella of coding theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of coding techniques, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper involves the use of mathematical analysis and optimization, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
